Place .patch files here to apply them to the Linux source tree during the build.
Patches are applied in filename sort order.

Naming convention:  NNNN-description.patch
  e.g.             0001-musl-compat-headers.patch
                   0002-disable-werror.patch

All patches must be unified diff format (diff -u or git format-patch).
They are applied with: patch -p1 < file.patch
from the root of the kernel source tree.
